@giuseppe The main reason to use btrfs driver is  that Fedora 33 / 34 / 35 use btrfs as filesystem and mounting  btrfs subvolumes to the path in btrfs subvolumes, btrfs path inside subvolumes to path, etc works without FUSE. As soon I tried to cross-filesystem mounts I got /run is not btrfs Fedora has 2-heads filesystem with /home and /root subvolumes with capabilities to do everything, more or less as rootless user. I followed to instructions how to configure storage.conf published by one of the Podman team member (driver + /home subvolume definition) and everything works when I use Podman in the CLI mode (Podman-pause scope is used as a head of CG hierarchy). But when containers are run by systemd unit the CG hierarchy is defined by the units dependencies. 
Podman knows to use BTRFS driver from the storage.conf. It stores all artifacts as subvolumes. How container runtime finds container subvolumes in the container storage  storage and storage and run root without reading the same config file?
When I run CRun as CLI I get the error mentioned above.Something is missing in parameters and environment passed to the service by unit from the Unit env configuration file.
